  "title": "Deploying and Using Gitlab in Kubernetes",
  "type": "lab",
  "description": "The article demonstrates how Gitlab deployment can be done in Kubernetes, using Redis, PostgreSQL, and Gitlab components. Knowledge points that will be covered include: PV Creation, Redis Deployment, PostgreSQL Deployment, Gitlab Deployment, Deployment Development, and Service Usage. To begin, a Kubernetes cluster with persistent storage needs to be set up, and the Redis persistent store needs to be created with a Redis service. The deployment status of Redis can be checked using `kubectl get po -n devops | grep redis`, and the status changes to running once deployed successfully. Finally, a Redis Service is created.",
